    • Constructor Detail

      • Position

        public Position(int x,
                int y)
        The x and y-values works as coordinates in the maze. The maze is made of a two-dimensional character array, and therefore, to move north, the y-axis has to be -1, and to go south the y-axis has to be +1 (to work with the indices of the matrix).
        Parameters:
        x - - the x-value that corresponds to the columns in the maze
        y - - the y-value that corresponds to the rows in the maze
